                        <property name="label" translatable="yes">Optodice requires a Discord Webhook URL to work.

If you roll some dice, the result will be send to the webhook
URL and the webhook then prints the result of your check 
to the channel he is assigned to.

&lt;b&gt;Creating a Discord Webhook:&lt;/b&gt;
To create a webhook for an Discord channel you need to have
the rights to do so. If you are not the owner/admin of the
channel, ask the administrator if he can create a webhook for
your party channel.
To create a webhook just right click the channel for which
you want to create a webhook. Then &lt;i&gt;Edit Channel&lt;/i&gt; -&gt;
&lt;i&gt;Integrations&lt;/i&gt; -&gt; &lt;i&gt;Create Webhook&lt;/i&gt;
You don't have to change name and avatar but be sure to
that the correct channel is selected. Then copy the webhook
URL and past it into the Optodice settings and send it to the 
other players.

Webhooks are just like simple bots that post everything you
send to there specific URL. So be aware to share your webhook
URL only with trustworthy users!
Only one webhook is required for a channel and every user can
use the same webhook.

Example setup the developers use:
 - one voice/video channel for the gameplay
 - one channel for adventure/story related data (maps, portraits,
   names of characters, quest log, etc.)
 - one channel for Optodice output (check results, character status...)</property>
